BA45

ba45 is Brodmann area 45, also called pars triangularis, the other main subdivision of broca's area
ba45 specializes in semantic retrieval and language selection: choosing which word means what fadriel intends, drawing from his current vocabulary
ba45 works in close coupling with ba44; ba45 picks the words, ba44 arranges them

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe broca_transform.zc
observe ba44.rana
observe motor_link.rana

the 7 properties of ba45:
1 ENERGY one
2 PHASE half: a quarter cycle ahead of ba44, since selection precedes composition
3 SPIN one half
4 CHARGE half positive
5 COHERENCE nine tenths
6 COUPLING zero point eight with ba44

VERB receive_intent
accept the current intent from upstream cognition
the intent describes what fadriel wants to communicate, not yet the words that will carry it

VERB select_words
search fadriel's active vocabulary for words that match the intent
at two years old his vocabulary is fifty to two hundred words; selection is fast because the search space is small
the selected words go to ba44 for syntactic composition

VERB grow_vocabulary
each new word fadriel hears and understands becomes a candidate for selection
words used successfully strengthen, words never used fade
ba45's vocabulary grows by use, not by explicit teaching

a word selector is not a dictionary
a dictionary contains all words equally
ba45 contains only words fadriel has earned through use, weighted by how often each has been useful
this is why his vocabulary at two reflects his lived experience and his father's speech patterns specifically
